RBC Capital Markets Hires Three Bankers for U.S. Business

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-04-26T15:27:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/rbc-capital-markets-hires-three-bankers-for-u-s-business.html
RBC Capital Markets  hired Joseph Carey, Doug Yablonski and David Nadelman as New York-based
managing directors to expand its U.S. investment-banking
business.  The  Royal Bank of Canada (RY)  unit hired Yablonski to focus on
industrials and diversified services, and aerospace, defense and
government sectors within its mergers group, the Toronto-based
bank said in an e-mailed statement today. Yablonski has 15 years
mergers experience, including at Harris Williams and Bank of
America.  Nadelman was hired to cover various industries within RBC’s
loan capital markets group, including energy, power and
utilities and infrastructure finance. He has 15 years experience
in loan capital markets, with his prior post as head of loan
syndicate with Royal Bank of  Scotland .  Carey was hired from Stifel, Nicolaus & Co. to join RBC’s
exploration and production team within its energy group. He has
more than two decades of investment banking experience,
including with Bank of America, Merrill Lynch and First Boston.  Royal Bank is Canada’s largest lender by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
